    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Senate Transportation Committee approved a bill yesterday to allocate $4 billion over four years for road, bridge and tunnel projects without raising the state gasoline tax.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Senate Transportation Committee approved a bill yesterday to allocate $4 billion over four years for road, bridge and tunnel projects without raising the state gasoline tax.</p>
        <p>The bill reauthorizes the state Transportation Trust Fund at a rate of $1 billion a year from 2001 though 2004, with money from the general fund. It must be approved by the full Assembly and Senate and Gov. Christine Todd Whitman.</p>
        <p>METRO NEWS BRIEFS: NEW JERSEY</p>
